title: NLL ICEs from 3rd crater run

labels.name: NLL-complete
labels.description: Working towards the "valid code works" goal

body:
Following on the ICEs from #52217, here are the 591 occurrences of ICEs in the [3rd NLL crater run](https://crater-reports.s3.amazonaws.com/pr-53426/index.html) from #53426 (out of the 982 regressions).

Only 2 kinds of ICEs this time:

- [x] 'scrape_region_constraints: incoming region obligations (#52992)
- [x] unresolved inference variable in outlives (#53568)

---

#### 1. 'scrape_region_constraints: incoming region obligations (#52992)

589 occurrences from what looks to be the known issue #52992. Thanks to @klemens the issue contains [a minimized repro](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/52992#issuecomment-410863330). For convenience, here's also the [playground link](https://play.rust-lang.org/?gist=96f9af515ace04f366b0c327d1564aff&version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2015) to that repro.

#### 2. unresolved inference variable in outlives: _#3t (https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/53568)

2 occurrences — but the 2nd crate fails because it depends on the 1st (`hyper-stub`) — and what looks like a possible more obscure case of #52057. 

This crate is small but pretty involved with its wrappers over hyper, tokio, and futures, resulting in a lot of associated types and bounds, and some of those 'static bounds might have a weird interaction with the NLL typeck, `impl Trait`, and maybe `delay_span_bug`. 

I've minimized it to only one such error, but note that the real code has 5 or 6 of them, so it would be good to verify any potential fix on the `hyper-stub` crate itself rather than just this minimized repro.
